# AI Reactor

## What it does

`code-server` environment focused on AI and data science. It includes a Python package set suitable for notebooks, lightweight training, prompt engineering, and ML prototyping.

## How to access it

- Compose profile: `workbench`
- Runtime URL: `${AI_DEV_URL}`
- Access mode: `password`
- Root password: `${AI_DEV_PASSWORD}`
- Activation command: `atlas-lab up --with-workbench`

## What is included

- Python stack with AI and data-science libraries
- Persistent workspace backed by a Docker volume
- A workflow that pairs well with `Open WebUI` and `Ollama`

## When to use it

- notebooks and proofs of concept
- local AI pipelines
- prompt and model evaluation
- data exploration

## Operational note

This workbench is the right place for code-centric AI development. `Open WebUI` remains the browser interaction console of the `ai-llm` layer and is only reachable when `--with-ai-llm` is also enabled.
